Description:
Set on a magnificent 1/4 acre
Set on a magnificent 1/4 acre (approx) or 1016 sqm within walking distance to the foreshore, beach, general store, walking tracks and Community Centre at Corinella, this is the perfect spot to build your new home or holiday house. Close to the highly regarded Bass Coast Primary school and only a stone's throw to Coronet Bay and the many attractions of Phillip Island, you can also explore the stunning ocean views at Kilcunda and enjoy village life at Inverloch. With the many amenities of Wonthaggi only 30 min away, you'll never have to travel far again. This the lowest priced land per sqm in Corinella and offers the best value for discerning buyers only.

Description:
6.2 Acre Property
Set on a perfect 6.2 acres of grassy paddocks with very few neighbours this one will appeal to the horse lover or those that just want some space to move. The home itself is spacious, bright and has had some updates already done, with 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and 2 large living zones.
With 3 spacious bedrooms, master with walk-in robe and ensuite, remaining bedrooms have built-in robes and are serviced by a huge family bathroom. Big enough for a larger family with a sizeable formal lounge at the front of the home and spacious open plan kitchen, living and dining area at the rear. The kitchen was updated recently and has ample bench space, plentiful cabinetry and stainless steel appliances. All overlooking a huge outdoor entertaining area with pergola and built-in fire place perfect to sit back, relax and watch the horses.
Other notable features include split system heating and cooling, horse round-yard, double garage plus additional large shed.

Description:
1/4 acre in Beautiful Corinella - Titled and Ready to Build
A good old fashioned 1/4 acre + block of land in gorgeous Corinella is available in Anderson Parade amongst homes on large blocks. Come and build your dream home on this whopping 1020 m2 approx block or keep it as an investment. This tranquil location so close to the water is surrounded by quality homes and is within walking distance to the heart of Corinella, close to walking tracks and minutes from the 24 hour boat ramp, Pier and bowling club. Corinella is at the gateway to Phillip Island and all that the surrounding area offers, wineries, restaurants, arts and so much more. With lots of interest in the area at present, this land represents great value.

Description:
4 Bedroom Family Home - Under Construction Now!
Ideally located in "The Grantville Rise Estate" - surrounded by all new homes, walking tracks, minutes walk to the foreshore & enjoy the great coffee & service that Grantville shops have to offer, as well as having easy access to public V-line transport. Close to all the boat ramps to enjoy the day out fishing on Western Port Bay! Under construction now, this house & land package includes Dishwasher, electric stainless steel hot cooking appliances hotplates & underbench oven, aluminium windows, holland blinds, flyscreens, TV antenna, full ensuite, Brivas split system airconditioning, tiles to the wet areas, quality carpets, grass turf to front yard, topsoil and seed to rear yard. Garage has a remote panel lift door. Fold down clothes line. This home is a turn key package, just move in enjoy & relax with the family! Approximately 1 hour 25 min to Melbourne and 20 mins to Phillip Island, Grantville Rise will be an easy escape from the city, and offers direct access via the Bass Hwy. For further details about this home and land package please click "email agent" link above.

Description:
FIXED PRICE BRAND NEW SIMONDS HOME
This beautiful brand new home from Simonds is to be built in the Eastern Shores Estate in central Grantville. Building will commence in approx. Jan, 2017. All the modern must haves are included, double garage with sectional overhead remote controlled door, colorbond roof and fencing with water tank.
A beautifully proportioned master suite at the front of the home includes a massive walk in robe, a relaxing ensuite bathroom and a split system air conditioner. A formal lounge room located at the front of the home could be utilized either for lounging, a study or media room.
Three other bedrooms are located close to the family area of the home and all have built in robes and are serviced by a family bathroom. Modern kitchen with all the mod cons including 900m gas range. Sliding door to the outdoors makes entertaining easy from the large family, dining areas of the home.
There will be colorbond fencing and a concrete driveway plus path to the front door. Make this yours, there are no progress payments involved.
Located at the gateway to the beautiful Bass Coast Eastern Shores is a comfortable 80 minute drive from Melbourne metropolitan and only 40 minutes commute to Pakenham and a short 15 min drive to Phillip Island and all that it has to offer. We can walk you through the same floor plan in a finished home on same estate, ring to inspect. No hidden price surprises! Pay 10% deposit, no progress payments, balance payment on completion.

Description:
DUAL OCCUPANCY or B & B OPPOSITE BEACHSIDE NATIONAL PARK
Our clients captured the feel of an outback station when they lovingly handcrafted these two adjacent homes from local materials.
An impressive long curved driveway bordered by immaculately trimmed hedges opens to a private treed garden plot offering privacy and protection to the cluster of buildings around the 2 homes. These include a 3 bay machine shed with large workshop containing a brand new 2.4 kw standalone solar power system and a separate smaller shed housing a 6.9 kva diesel backup generator. The potable water supply is provided by 20,000 gallons of rain water storage collected from all roofs.
Once a bush block, this 75 acre property now has everything you need to live independently on the Island with abundant quality bore water and irrigated watering system for crops, pasture with 2 dams fenced to 2 paddocks with shelter trees for livestock, a small orchard, large igloo style hot house, fully enclosed vegie patch and a wood lot for heating in winter.
Main dwelling has master bedroom off main living area plus 2nd bedroom, main bathroom and an open plan living area with cathedral ceilings with exposed natural timber beams.
The guests' wing provides two additional bedrooms both with en-suite and a central kitchen/living area; ideally set up as a separate bed and breakfast. The two homes are connected by a wide veranda.
Delightful outlook across your own acreage situated close to ferry opposite walking track through National Park to private beach and nothing to do but move in.
Your inspection recommended by contacting Phil Bock on 0438 497 715 who will meet you at the ferry.

Address: Lot 2 Dunbbabin Road The Gurdies VIC 3984
Description:
50 ACRES LIFESTYLE/HOBBY FARMLET BAY VIEWS
This is a most appealing parcel of gently undulating clean grazing land with bitumen road access and sweeping bay views and just over an hour to Melbourne in an emerging lifestyle region and close to local wineries, restaurants and tourism attractions. Main features include:
- 50 acres all cleared, excellent well managed clean pastures, gentle undulation,
- 1 hour approx.. to Melbourne, bay views, bitumen road, power on site, tanks,
- Good fencing, several paddocks, 3 spring fed dams, neat and fenced off and treed,
- Excellent new gal/iron cattle yards, crush and loading ramps,
- Large colour bond shed 15M x 8M, concrete power, water tank, fenced off,
- Fabulous building sites throughout (STCA)
